abstract: A few hundred people and no arrests in a march that ends up before the U.S. Chamber of Commerce.
snippet: A few hundred people and no arrests in a march that ends up before the U.S. Chamber of Commerce.
lead_paragraph: Surrounded by camouflage-clad veterans with peace signs sewn into their clothing, a man dressed as a "corporate pig" and the aptly named Raging Grannies, Gary Wood used a portion of his vacation to attend the Washington spillover of the Occupy Wall Street protests. He found that he agreed with what he took to be the movement's message.
